strategy_text:
Casters and healers, spread out behind the boss, so you don't all take impale damage. 

If you get impaled and fly, don't die from fall damage, use blink or lip or healthstone or anything you can to stay alive.

If you are high on threat, swap to the adds.

Kill the 2 followers fast (Skull and Cross), then nuke boss. Move out of rain of fire.

Assigned priests use mind control and Widow's Embrace to dispel Enrage from the boss.

Kill the 2 followers fast (Skull and Cross), then nuke boss. Move out of rain of fire.

Assigned priests use mind control and Widow's Embrace to dispel Enrage from the boss.
When you have a tanking target, go defensive stand, taunt and bloodthirst. Once you have agro you can swap to berserker if you can survive it.
Shamans, bounce chain heals of your tank assignment. Keep them alive. Priests and Druids, keep your tank alive.

Nuke the boss. Shamans and druids, remove poison. HoT and Shield on tank before Web Spray. Tank use last stand, Lifegiving gem etc.

Do not hit the boss in the face, only pound his ass. Let the tank turn it around before you zug zug.
Priests pull with mind control. Off-tanks tank adds. Mana users run out before Disruption Shout. Melee throw target dummies when needed.
Warriors on Undead side. Ranged and Rogues on Human side. Pop Greater Stoneshield on wave 9. We don't shackle. Healers

We nuke down and commit on Thane.

Healer rotation starts on first mark and then healers all roather on every 3rd mark.
